Get new abbreviations

Source: R/fn_get.R
get_new_abbrs.Rd

get_new_abbrs() is a Get function that retrieves a pre-existing data object from memory, local file system or online repository. Specifically, this function implements an algorithm to get new abbreviations. Function argument pkg_setup_ls specifies the where to look for the required object. The function returns New abbreviations (a character vector).

get_new_abbrs(
  pkg_setup_ls,
  classes_to_make_tb = NULL,
  inc_all_mthds_1L_lgl = T,
  paths_ls = make_fn_nms(),
  pkg_ds_ls_ls = NULL,
  transformations_chr = NULL,
  undocumented_fns_dir_chr = make_undmtd_fns_dir_chr(drop_empty_1L_lgl = T),
  use_last_1L_int = NULL,
  fns_dmt_tb = deprecated()
)

Arguments

pkg_setup_ls

Package setup (a list)
classes_to_make_tb

Classes to make (a tibble), Default: NULL
inc_all_mthds_1L_lgl

Include all methods (a logical vector of length one), Default: T
paths_ls

Paths (a list), Default: make_fn_nms()
pkg_ds_ls_ls

Package dataset (a list of lists), Default: NULL
transformations_chr

Transformations (a character vector), Default: NULL
undocumented_fns_dir_chr

Undocumented functions directory (a character vector), Default: make_undmtd_fns_dir_chr(drop_empty_1L_lgl = T)
use_last_1L_int

Use last (an integer vector of length one), Default: NULL
fns_dmt_tb

Functions documentation (a tibble), Default: deprecated()

Value

New abbreviations (a character vector)
